It seems due to the different behavior of pseudo classes in Edge. Maybe the different CSS engines used in different browsers caused the issue. 

You could change the below code:

    /* ERROR STATE ================================= */
    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar::before,
    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar::after {
        background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 1);
    }

into:

    /* ERROR STATE ================================= */
    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar::before,
    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar {
        background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 1);
    }

    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar::after,
    .md-input-group input.error ~ .bar {
        background: rgba(255, 0, 0, 1);
    }

Then it will be work in Edge.

