You can also use `degit` - a scaffolding tool - to start from a template project as explained [here][1]. This will generate the `public` directory and the `index.html` file, among others, for you.

The template is really very bare bones (a good thing in my opinion). See for yourself:
```html
&lt;!doctype html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
	&lt;meta charset=&#39;utf-8&#39;&gt;
	&lt;meta name=&#39;viewport&#39; content=&#39;width=device-width&#39;&gt;

	&lt;title&gt;Svelte app&lt;/title&gt;

	&lt;link rel=&#39;icon&#39; type=&#39;image/png&#39; href=&#39;/favicon.png&#39;&gt;
	&lt;link rel=&#39;stylesheet&#39; href=&#39;/global.css&#39;&gt;
	&lt;link rel=&#39;stylesheet&#39; href=&#39;/bundle.css&#39;&gt;

